“With the support of the UK government, donors, national governments, and Global Citizens just like you, we can make social injustice or malnutrition a footnote in history,” The Power of Nutrition Ambassador Tracey Ullman told the crowd at a live 2018 concert in London.
The group also said that after more than 5,000 actions calling on the UK to improve the nutrition of mothers and children, the government announced the expansion of funds for a project, the Power of Nutrition, which will reach 5 million women and children through interventions in favor of nutrition.
In response to one of the FAQs on his website, he asked, “What makes you think we can end extreme poverty?”
Global Citizen responded: “It will be a long and arduous journey – sometimes we will fail and we will fail.
But, like the great civil rights and anti-apartheid movements before us, we will succeed, because together we are stronger.
